[[File:Oshima-swamyolin3.JPG|thumb|150px|right|Banners ({{ill|Hengaku|ja|扁額}}) reading “{{ill|Ishikateo Shrine|ja|石楯尾神社}}”]]
'''Suwa Myōjin''' (諏訪明神, すわみょうじん) is a Shinto shrine located on Oshima in Midori Ward, Sagamihara City, {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県}}. It is also known as “Oshima Suwa Myōjin” or “Osuwa-sama”. In the publication 『{{ill|Sagamihara Fudoki-kō|ja|相模原風土記稿}}』 (Shrine section) by the Sagamihara City Board of Education, it is referred to as “{{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社}}”.<ref>[http://www.ne.jp/asahi/zama/nobi/new_page_2.htm {{ill|Suwa Myōjin|ja|諏訪明神}}] (Roots Zama: Nobi Column){{ill|Link broken|ja|リンク切れ|lt=Link broken|lt_ja=リンク切れ}}, November 2021</ref>

== 祭神 ==
* {{ill|Mihosusumi-no-Mikoto|ja|御穂須々美命}} (Mihosusumi-no-Mikoto)
* Within the shrine precincts at the Yasaka-sha: {{ill|Yasaka Tomeredomi-no-Mikoto|ja|八坂刀売之命|lt=Yasaka Tomeredomi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=八坂刀売之命}}

== 境内社 ==
* An Inari shrine dedicated to {{ill|Ukano Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦之御魂神}}

== 歴史 ==
According to tradition, this shrine was established by a monk of the Buddhist order (Kakushinshi) during the {{ill|Eishō era|ja|永正年間}} (1504–1521). It was later rebuilt in {{ill|Hōei 7|ja|宝永7年}} (1710) and became the collective tutelary shrine for the former Oshima Village and the former Kūsawa Village. It is also said that one of the 13 shrines listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳}} for Sagami Province (【13 Zoa of Sagami】) is “{{ill|Ishikateo Shrine|ja|石楯尾神社}}”, which some scholars argue may refer to this shrine; however, this identification remains uncertain.<ref>{{sfn|Shinpen Sagami Fudoki-kō, Oshima Village Suwa-sha|ja|新編相模国風土記稿 大島村 諏訪社}}</ref>

== 祭事 ==
* The annual festival and lion dance ({{ill|Shishi-mai|ja|獅子舞}}) are held on the last Sunday in August (originally on {{ill|August 26|ja|8月26日}}). 
* At the festival, a lion dance is performed, which has been designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property by Kanagawa Prefecture and as a registered intangible folk cultural property by Sagamihara City. Three types of lions (sword lion, rolled lion, and ball lion [female lion]) are seen dancing in coordination with a flutist and chanter, along with roles for red ogre, tengu, and clowns portrayed by Okazaki.

== 交通 ==
* From either the south exit of {{ill|Hashimoto Station (Kanagawa)|ja|橋本駅 (神奈川県)}} or the south exit of {{ill|Sagamihara Station|ja|相模原駅}}, take the bus bound for “Kami Oshima” and get off at “Kami Oshima.”

== 周辺 ==
* {{ill|Chōtoku-ji (Sagamihara)|ja|長徳寺 (相模原市)}}

