* Within the shrine precincts at the Yasaka-sha: {{ill|Yasaka Tomeredomi-no-Mikoto|ja|八坂刀売之命|lt=Yasaka Tomeredomi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=八坂刀売之命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasaka Tomeredomi-no-Mikoto|qq=}}

== Sub-shrines ==
* An Inari shrine dedicated to {{ill|Ukano Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦之御魂神|1=Ukanomitama|2=ja|3=ウカノミタマ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukano Mitama-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=}}

== History ==
According to tradition, this shrine was established by a monk of the Buddhist order (Kakushinshi) during the {{ill|Eishō era|ja|永正年間|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eishō era|qq=}} (1504–1521). It was later rebuilt in {{ill|Hōei 7|ja|宝永7th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei 7|qq=}} (1710) and became the collective tutelary shrine for the former Oshima Village and the former Kūsawa Village. It is also said that one of the 13 shrines listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} for Sagami Province (【13 Zoa of Sagami】) is “{{ill|Ishikateo Shrine|ja|石楯尾神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikateo Shrine|qq=}}”, which some scholars argue may refer to this shrine; however, this identification remains uncertain.<ref>{{sfn|Shinpen Sagami Fudoki-kō, Oshima Village Suwa-sha|ja|新編相模国風土記稿 大島村 諏訪社}}</ref>

== Festivals ==
* The annual festival and lion dance ({{ill|Shishi-mai|ja|獅子舞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shishi-mai|qq=}}) are held on the last Sunday in August (originally on {{ill|August 26|ja|8月26日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/August 26|qq=}}). 
* At the festival, a lion dance is performed, which has been designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property by Kanagawa Prefecture and as a registered intangible folk cultural property by Sagamihara City. Three types of lions (sword lion, rolled lion, and ball lion [female lion]) are seen dancing in coordination with a flutist and chanter, along with roles for red ogre, tengu, and clowns portrayed by Okazaki.
== 交通 ==
* From either the south exit of {{ill|Hashimoto Station (Kanagawa)|ja|橋本駅 (神奈川県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hashimoto Station (Kanagawa)|qq=}} or the south exit of {{ill|Sagamihara Station|ja|相模原駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sagamihara Station|qq=}}, take the bus bound for “Kami Oshima” and get off at “Kami Oshima.”

