'''Suwa Myōjin''' (諏訪明神, すわみょうじん) is a Shinto shrine located on Oshima in Midori Ward, Sagamihara City, [[:en:Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa Prefecture]]. It is also known as “Oshima Suwa Myōjin” or “Osuwa-sama”. In the publication 『{{ill|Sagamihara Fudoki-kō|ja|相模原風土記稿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sagamihara Fudoki-kō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}』 (Shrine section) by the Sagamihara City Board of Education, it is referred to as “{{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Shrine|qq=}}”.<ref>[http://www.ne.jp/asahi/zama/nobi/new_page_2.htm {{ill|Suwa Myōjin|ja|諏訪明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Myōjin|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 諏訪神社|1=Suwa Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2370082}}] (Roots Zama: Nobi Column)[[:en:Link rot|Link broken]], November 2021</ref>

